cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the robustness of classifiers to naturally occurring perturbations of images found in videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also evaluates a diverse array of classifiers trained on ImageNet, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the challenges posed by natural perturbations in safety-critical environments, which could fall under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper deals with images found in videos, which could also fall under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
